# ============================================================
# COMPANY ROLE ARCHITECTURE
# ============================================================

status: canonical
layer: architecture
domain: company
scope: company.role
system: civilization-os
owner: Boss
prepared_by: Zero

## purpose
Defines role structure inside company.

## role_model
Company role structure must separate
ownership,
strategic authority,
execution authority,
review authority,
and integration authority.

## actor_matrix
- owner
- executive
- operator
- reviewer
- regulator
- adapter

## role_rules
- ownership does not automatically imply operational execution
- execution authority does not automatically imply review authority
- review authority must remain explicit
- integration adapters may act only within bounded delegation
- role overlap must remain reviewable

## delegation_rules
A role may delegate bounded action,
but delegation must preserve
origin authority,
scope,
duration,
and reviewability.

## role_conflict_rules
If two roles produce contradictory authority outcomes,
the company path must stop and route to review.

## example_scenarios
- owner appoints executive without granting unrestricted review authority
- operator executes bounded company activity
- reviewer blocks out-of-scope company action
- integration adapter transmits bounded company state externally

## review_checklist
- roles are distinct
- delegation is bounded
- review authority is explicit
- conflict handling is explicit
